OL,7,FInterjecting in line of questioning,
OL,8,Fthe inquiry chairman Sir Wyn Williams
OL,9,Fsaid: "As it happens Mr Daily, your
OL,10,Fevidence about the searches and
OL,11,Finvestigations you conducted to, as
OL,12,Fyou then thought and as you've told
OL,13,Fme, discover where the money was, they
OL,14,Fwere quite thorough and yet you found
OL,15,Fnothing.
OL,17,F"In light of that, did that not give
OL,18,Fadded credence to Mr Holmes'
OL,19,Fsuggestion that this was generated by
OL,20,Fthe computer as opposed to being real?"
OL,26,@qD@GOUyD@AOU|D@gO]
